  "texts": [
    "A key challenge is developing interoperable and fair economic frameworks across heterogeneous IoA platforms with varying protocols and value models.",
    "F. Trustworthy Regulation in IoAAs AI agents gain increasing autonomy and direct influence over both digital and physical environments, ensuring trust, safety, and ethical compliance in the IoA becomes critical.",
    "Unlike conventional IoT devices, agents can autonomously make decisions, initiate actions, and interact with other agents in complex ways, yet they lack legal accountability.",
    "Therefore, IoA requires trustworthy regulatory mechanisms that can verify agent identities, govern their behaviors, and safeguard against malicious activities.",
    "Potential IoA regulation technologies include DIDs, blockchain, and legal regulations, as below.1) Accountability of AI Agents."
